description.narrative: (Zimbabwe): The integrated maternal newborn and child health (MNCH) and family planning (FP) activity will target Manicaland with intensive MNCH and malaria support and provide comprehensive FP services nationwide. The objectives of this activity are to:.Improve quality of MNCH-FP and malaria services;Increase use of MNCH-FP and malaria services among hard-to-reach populations;Strengthen community systems and linkages to integrated MNCH-FP services; andImprove national capacity for policy implementation.The activity will strengthen the capacity of healthcare workers to provide a continuum of respectful and quality care that is responsive to the needs of hard-to-reach populations, especially adolescents and apostolic communities, with optimized links connecting health facilities and communities. .Using FY 2020 funds, the activity will:.Strengthen health worker knowledge and skills to deliver high-impact MNCH, FP, and malaria interventions through training, mentorship, and supervision; Support village health workers to expand MNCH and FP service delivery and strengthen malaria case management;Deliver FP services in remote areas via outreach and mobile clinics;Improve linkages between health facilities and communities;Strengthen the functioning of health center committees;Address barriers to service uptake via community dialogues;Support routine immunizations and introduction of new vaccines; andSupport the Ministry of Health and Child Care (MOHCC) national policy formulation and implementation..This activity will improve demand for and the availability of quality MNCH-FP and malaria services in the seven districts of Manicaland Province; increase access to FP nationwide; and improve MOHCC's and the Zimbabwe National Family Planning Council's (ZNFPC) capacity for policy formulation and implementation...
